00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:27,720
What we've brought today

288
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,320
is the very first batch of paper

289
00:13:31,240 --> 00:13:33,440
each of you made after joining the Xuan Family

290
00:13:33,520 --> 00:13:35,080
Please take them home

291
00:13:35,480 --> 00:13:36,640
as a keepsake

292
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:39,400
The Xuan Family will always be your home

293
00:13:39,720 --> 00:13:40,600
And you

294
00:13:40,920 --> 00:13:43,360
will always be family to us

295
00:13:45,360 --> 00:13:47,040
Please, masters, be seated

296
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:57,000
Ye Shengkai

297
00:14:01,240 --> 00:14:03,560
On March 17th, 1982

298
00:14:04,400 --> 00:14:06,920
you became an apprentice at the Xuan Family

299
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:09,120
More than forty years have passed

300
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:12,080
We present you the first batch you ever made

301
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:15,600
Please take care, Master Ye

302
00:14:26,560 --> 00:14:27,480
Mei Sulan

303
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:32,480
On September 19th, 1994

304
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:34,480
you became an apprentice at the Xuan Family

305
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:37,320
Now, over thirty-two years later

306
00:14:38,440 --> 00:14:39,960
we present you the very first batch

307
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:42,280
you dried after joining us

308
00:14:44,120 --> 00:14:45,480
Please take good care

309
00:14:49,480 --> 00:14:50,320
Hu Wanjin

310
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:54,080
On the first day of May, 1999

311
00:14:54,320 --> 00:14:56,400
you became an apprentice at the Xuan Family

312
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:59,480
Now, over twenty-seven years later

313
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:03,200
we present the first batch you dried after joining

314
00:15:03,440 --> 00:15:04,720
Please take good care

315
00:15:06,720 --> 00:15:07,760
Thank you, senior brother

316
00:15:31,160 --> 00:15:31,800
Old Xuan

317
00:15:33,240 --> 00:15:34,240
And to all the masters here

318
00:15:35,600 --> 00:15:38,440
Three generations of my Man family worked at Hongxing Factory

319
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:39,920
Now with Xiao Man's generation

320
00:15:40,760 --> 00:15:42,440
I've sent him to the Xuan Family

321
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:46,480
to inherit the thousand-year legacy of the Xuan Family

322
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:50,160
to learn how to be a man, how to make paper,

323
00:15:50,320 --> 00:15:51,280
and the principles behind it all

324
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:55,200
Brother Yongnian graciously took him in as an apprentice

325
00:15:55,920 --> 00:15:59,000
treating him like his own and teaching him everything

326
00:15:59,000 --> 00:15:59,440
I

327
00:16:01,200 --> 00:16:02,480
am deeply grateful

328
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:04,440
May the generations to come

329
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:06,080
wherever they may go

330
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:09,160
carry on the Xuan paper culture through generations

331
00:16:09,160 --> 00:16:10,320
with all their heart and soul

332
00:16:10,760 --> 00:16:13,880
I, Man Chenggui, thank you all here today

333
00:16:53,880 --> 00:16:55,600
Master, you have to go slow, slow, slow.

334
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:57,160
Slow, slow, slow.

335
00:16:58,760 --> 00:16:59,360
Okay.

336
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:02,280
Careful, careful, careful.

337
00:17:08,880 --> 00:17:09,640
Uncle Xuan.

338
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:12,400
I truly understand how you feel right now.

339
00:17:12,720 --> 00:17:14,760
But we're just following the rules.

340
00:17:14,839 --> 00:17:16,119
I hope you can understand.

341
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:29,120
But...

342
00:17:30,520 --> 00:17:32,240
what am I supposed to pass down?

343
00:17:34,360 --> 00:17:39,320
My ancestors passed this great legacy to me.

344
00:17:39,720 --> 00:17:40,480
I've been thinking

345
00:17:40,760 --> 00:17:44,360
about how to carry this treasure forward.

346
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:47,080
It keeps spinning in my mind.

347
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:49,840
We keep saying "good paper, good paper,"

348
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:51,480
but we can't make good Xuan paper.

349
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:53,040
We keep saying "run the business,"

350
00:17:53,040 --> 00:17:55,120
but we can't run it into anything good either.

351
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:56,280
From now on,

352
00:17:56,280 --> 00:17:58,120
you don't have to pay me wages.

353
00:17:58,120 --> 00:18:01,160
Being here, learning the craft with Master,

354
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:02,640
and not being charged tuition,

355
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:03,880
I'm already coming out ahead.

356
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:05,360
Whenever the Xuan Family needs us,

357
00:18:05,360 --> 00:18:06,880
that's when we'll come back.

358
00:18:06,880 --> 00:18:07,760
No matter where we go,

359
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:09,120
wherever we end up,

360
00:18:09,120 --> 00:18:10,480
we're always Xuan Family people.

361
00:18:10,880 --> 00:18:12,920
We're running a business, not a charity.

362
00:18:12,920 --> 00:18:15,520
That's just the basic rule of survival.

363
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:17,880
The company has to survive first,

364
00:18:18,160 --> 00:18:19,360
so the workers can have food on the table,

365
00:18:19,360 --> 00:18:20,760
and we can secure employment.

366
00:18:21,160 --> 00:18:23,320
Whether traditional Xuan paper has a future,

367
00:18:23,320 --> 00:18:24,720
you know that better than anyone.

368
00:18:25,360 --> 00:18:27,160
Let's still make authentic Xuan paper.

369
00:18:27,240 --> 00:18:28,880
Whatever way's best, that's how we'll do it.

370
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:11,480
Dad.

371
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:14,760
Don't worry.

372
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:15,960
Trust me.

373
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:17,880
Our Xuan Family

374
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:20,280
will definitely bounce back.

375
00:19:24,040 --> 00:19:25,480
You little brat!

376
00:19:25,960 --> 00:19:27,200
This slap I just gave you,

377
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:28,600
it's to make you remember,

378
00:19:29,400 --> 00:19:30,280
in our Xuan Family,

379
00:19:30,280 --> 00:19:31,720
there have never been any "workers,"

380
00:19:31,720 --> 00:19:32,880
or any "hired hands."

381
00:19:32,920 --> 00:19:34,640
They're all your uncles and aunts,

382
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:36,280
your own flesh and blood.

383
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:38,760
They're the pillars holding up the Xuan Family,

384
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:40,040
the roots of the Xuan Family.

385
00:19:44,760 --> 00:19:47,080
And those "cultural products" you've been fooling with

386
00:19:47,520 --> 00:19:49,920
have driven the Xuan Family to this state.

387
00:19:50,280 --> 00:19:51,280
Our Xuan Family

388
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:53,520
was torn apart and ruined

389
00:19:53,920 --> 00:19:55,280
by you, this good-for-nothing!

390
00:20:11,880 --> 00:20:13,720
Master has struggled to hold on for years.

391
00:20:13,760 --> 00:20:15,000
His only hope in this life

392
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,720
is to keep the Xuan Family tree standing strong,

393
00:20:16,720 --> 00:20:18,040
to keep it alive.

394
00:20:18,720 --> 00:20:20,760
You know full well the roots are already rotten.

395
00:20:20,760 --> 00:20:21,800
One strong gust and it falls.

396
00:20:21,800 --> 00:20:23,280
Yet you had to go and shake it.

397
00:20:29,480 --> 00:20:30,160
Brother Min.

398
00:20:31,800 --> 00:20:32,880
Was I wrong?

399
00:20:46,040 --> 00:20:46,760
Yes, I was wrong.

400
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:48,600
I was wrong

401
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:50,760
because I didn't put myself in his shoes

402
00:20:50,760 --> 00:20:52,440
to consider my father's feelings.

403
00:20:53,280 --> 00:20:55,400
I was wrong for not putting myself in their place

404
00:20:56,600 --> 00:20:58,280
to think about how the masters feel.

405
00:20:58,840 --> 00:21:00,240
But all I wanted

406
00:21:01,280 --> 00:21:02,840
was to keep Xuan paper

407
00:21:02,840 --> 00:21:05,160
from having only tradition as its path.

408
00:21:05,160 --> 00:21:07,760
I wanted Xuan paper to run on two legs.

409
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:09,480
Why is that so hard?

410
00:21:11,720 --> 00:21:12,600
Why?

411
00:21:13,320 --> 00:21:15,040
Why did it have to end like this?

412
00:21:20,320 --> 00:21:21,840
The Xuan paper market is bad.

413
00:21:22,520 --> 00:21:23,920
Times are tough for the Xuan Family.

414
00:21:23,920 --> 00:21:25,000
You've all done your best.

415
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:26,000
I know that.

416
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:28,400
But of all things, you should never,

417
00:21:30,320 --> 00:21:32,280
never have caused this disaster.

418
00:21:34,160 --> 00:21:35,920
How is Master supposed to go on?

419
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:38,680
Old Xuan.

420
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:42,040
Dayazhai ordered a ton of Jingpi paper first.

421
00:22:42,160 --> 00:22:43,440
The money is already in.

422
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:44,200
In a month,

423
00:22:44,200 --> 00:22:45,160
they'll order another ton.

424
00:22:46,440 --> 00:22:47,760
Oh my goodness!

425
00:22:47,760 --> 00:22:49,320
That's two tons total!

426
00:22:49,440 --> 00:22:50,760
Money to be made, and he's complaining?

427
00:22:50,760 --> 00:22:51,640
Exactly.

428
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:52,440
Business is booming.

429
00:22:52,440 --> 00:22:54,120
We're happy to work overtime.

430
00:22:54,120 --> 00:22:55,440
Just get to work quickly.

431
00:22:55,440 --> 00:22:56,880
Right, let's get to work.

432
00:22:57,440 --> 00:22:59,560
Anyway, I'll handle the logistics.

433
00:22:59,840 --> 00:23:01,040
I've made up my mind.

434
00:23:01,840 --> 00:23:03,280
I've decided.

435
00:23:03,280 --> 00:23:05,440
If this partnership succeeds,

436
00:23:05,560 --> 00:23:07,880
I'll definitely give everyone a raise.

437
00:23:18,440 --> 00:23:19,240
Master.

438
00:23:19,240 --> 00:23:20,160
What's this?

439
00:23:22,000 --> 00:23:23,000
You don't recognize it?

440
00:23:23,960 --> 00:23:25,400
Of course I do.

441
00:23:25,440 --> 00:23:27,320
This is the one from the back mountain,

442
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:29,440
the stone mortar from the old workshop.

443
00:23:29,920 --> 00:23:30,720
That's right.

444
00:23:31,120 --> 00:23:32,120
I brought it down.

445
00:23:33,040 --> 00:23:35,640
This thing weighs at least 300 pounds.

446
00:23:36,440 --> 00:23:37,760
Why did you bring this down?

447
00:23:39,280 --> 00:23:40,080
I think,

448
00:23:40,760 --> 00:23:42,760
this was left by the Xuan Family ancestors.

449
00:23:43,280 --> 00:23:45,720
It can't just sit out there in the wilderness.

450
00:26:17,320 --> 00:26:18,920
Here, slow down.

451
00:26:24,440 --> 00:26:27,520
You go ahead. Let me catch my breath.

452
00:26:40,040 --> 00:26:40,840
Senior brother.

453
00:26:43,800 --> 00:26:44,520
Senior brother.

454
00:26:47,520 --> 00:26:48,240
Senior brother.

455
00:26:49,120 --> 00:26:50,040
Time to eat.

456
00:26:50,800 --> 00:26:52,760
Look how high the sun is already.

457
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:53,800
And you're still sleeping?

458
00:26:54,320 --> 00:26:55,160
Get up.

459
00:27:07,920 --> 00:27:08,600
Senior brother.

460
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:12,080
Seems ever since the factory stopped running,

461
00:27:12,520 --> 00:27:15,080
you can't sleep at night either,

462
00:27:15,080 --> 00:27:16,240
and can't wake up during the day.

463
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:25,240
What about Yongnian?

464
00:27:25,520 --> 00:27:27,080
He's not much better than you.

465
00:27:27,280 --> 00:27:29,040
Can't sleep at night either.

466
00:27:29,440 --> 00:27:31,480
But during the day, he's not in bed.

467
00:27:31,480 --> 00:27:33,680
He's practically welded to the paper-scooping workshop.

468
00:27:33,680 --> 00:27:35,080
Doesn't come back all day.

469
00:27:37,080 --> 00:27:37,880
Go eat.

470
00:27:38,520 --> 00:27:39,760
I've made everything already.

471
00:27:40,320 --> 00:27:41,120
Let's go.

472
00:27:47,680 --> 00:27:49,000
I've brewed your tea.

473
00:27:58,680 --> 00:27:59,400
Lin Yiran.

474
00:28:01,400 --> 00:28:02,000
Yiran.

475
00:28:02,760 --> 00:28:03,600
Director Liao.

476
00:28:05,760 --> 00:28:07,040
Have you heard about the Xuan Family?

477
00:28:08,040 --> 00:28:08,840
Heard what?

478
00:28:12,360 --> 00:28:14,200
Wait, wait, what happened?

479
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:16,000
The Xuan Family's factory went under.

480
00:28:17,280 --> 00:28:18,000
No way, this...

481
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:19,440
When did this happen?

482
00:28:19,840 --> 00:28:21,080
Xuan Yan took over the business.

483
00:28:21,200 --> 00:28:22,520
He pushed changes too fast.

484
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:25,240
The workers couldn't adjust and all left.

485
00:28:28,480 --> 00:28:30,680
How could Xuan Yan make such a huge mistake?

486
00:28:32,080 --> 00:28:33,120
He didn't want it to happen either.

487
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:34,560
Yiran.

488
00:28:35,600 --> 00:28:36,440
If you have time,

489
00:28:37,240 --> 00:28:38,160
go see him.

490
00:28:42,840 --> 00:28:44,320
It must be because of what happened last time.

491
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:47,280
It took too great a toll on Uncle Xuan's health.

492
00:28:48,520 --> 00:28:49,320
He had no choice.

493
00:28:49,320 --> 00:28:50,760
That's why he had Xuan Yan take over.

494
00:28:53,920 --> 00:28:54,560
So, Yiran,

495
00:28:55,240 --> 00:28:56,960
don't stay gloomy all day.

496
00:28:57,200 --> 00:28:59,120
Burying yourself in work to cope,

497
00:28:59,920 --> 00:29:01,200
how long can you keep it up?

498
00:29:02,280 --> 00:29:03,080
Sooner or later,

499
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:05,600
you'll still have to face him.

500
00:29:40,120 --> 00:29:40,920
Secretary Wu.

501
00:29:41,560 --> 00:29:43,520
Yes, yes, I'm on my way. Almost there.

502
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:45,920
Right, have them go ahead and

503
00:29:46,400 --> 00:29:47,800
print out the planning materials first.

504
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:48,840
Okay, okay, I'll be right there.

505
00:30:43,080 --> 00:30:43,840
I can't, I can't anymore.

506
00:30:44,480 --> 00:30:45,600
My shoulder, it can't take it.

507
00:30:45,800 --> 00:30:47,040
Put it down, put it down!

508
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:03,160
Thanks.

509
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:20,320
Every single day you're here,

510
00:31:21,280 --> 00:31:21,840
it's like this,

511
00:31:24,200 --> 00:31:25,040
day after day.

512
00:31:26,400 --> 00:31:27,200
Do I like it?

513
00:31:29,280 --> 00:31:30,080
Not really.

514
00:31:30,960 --> 00:31:31,760
Do I hate it?

515
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:34,240
Not really either.

516
00:31:35,960 --> 00:31:37,400
Then what does it feel like?

517
00:31:40,280 --> 00:31:41,440
Honestly, I don't feel much.

518
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:49,440
Aren't you gonna ask

519
00:31:49,440 --> 00:31:50,840
why I suddenly came over?

520
00:31:52,400 --> 00:31:54,600
You'll tell me when you want to.

521
00:31:56,720 --> 00:31:58,400
Talking to you is such a chore.

522
00:31:59,080 --> 00:32:00,280
Just spending this little time with you,

523
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:02,480
I've used up all my words for the month.

524
00:32:09,720 --> 00:32:10,080
Come on.

525
00:32:11,440 --> 00:32:12,440
Okay, I can do it.

526
00:32:14,560 --> 00:32:15,600
Alright, let's go.

527
00:32:38,280 --> 00:32:39,320
Withered lotus.

528
00:32:46,080 --> 00:32:48,520
Though this is freshly dried paper,

529
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:49,920
just look at it.

530
00:32:50,480 --> 00:32:53,200
In dense strokes, it holds great weight.

531
00:32:53,760 --> 00:32:57,000
In faint ones, it captures cloud shadows.

532
00:32:58,520 --> 00:32:59,520
What a pity.

533
00:33:00,080 --> 00:33:03,000
The paper you make is like this withered lotus.

534
00:33:03,440 --> 00:33:04,720
Withered stems about to break,

535
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:07,000
wind sweeping the remaining leaves,

536
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:08,520
a pond of aging years.

537
00:33:08,520 --> 00:33:10,880
Retire and enjoy your peace.

538
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:13,040
It's time to step down.

539
00:33:26,800 --> 00:33:27,840
You old rascal.

540
00:33:27,840 --> 00:33:29,000
When did you

541
00:33:29,200 --> 00:33:31,760
sneak in here so quietly?

542
00:33:32,280 --> 00:33:33,600
What is it? What's the matter?

543
00:33:33,840 --> 00:33:34,360
Go on.

544
00:33:42,160 --> 00:33:43,440
Yes, yes, yes.

545
00:33:43,520 --> 00:33:44,960
Everyone's gone, the place is empty.

546
00:33:44,960 --> 00:33:46,240
The factory's gone.

547
00:33:46,720 --> 00:33:48,560
It's become so quiet and desolate.

548
00:33:49,600 --> 00:33:50,840
It's fine, it's fine.

549
00:33:53,160 --> 00:33:54,240
Just not used to it, that's all.

550
00:33:55,040 --> 00:33:56,240
From being unaccustomed

551
00:33:58,040 --> 00:33:58,960
to getting used to it.

552
00:33:59,920 --> 00:34:00,480
Yongnian.

553
00:34:01,240 --> 00:34:03,200
How much money have I saved with you?

554
00:34:07,040 --> 00:34:08,520
I don't really know.

555
00:34:08,520 --> 00:34:11,679
Because Xiumei's the one managing the money.

556
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:12,760
What's wrong?

557
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:18,000
There's nothing for me to do at this factory.

558
00:34:19,239 --> 00:34:21,360
I can't stand eating here without earning my keep.

559
00:34:22,320 --> 00:34:23,960
How many times have we been over this?

560
00:34:27,280 --> 00:34:29,520
You want to leave? Where would you even go?

561
00:34:29,760 --> 00:34:30,719
Back to your hometown?

562
00:34:31,320 --> 00:34:33,239
You don't have any family left there.

563
00:34:33,719 --> 00:34:34,679
What would you go back for?

564
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:37,000
No one there to even look after you.

565
00:34:38,480 --> 00:34:39,920
If Sister Min were still around,

566
00:34:41,239 --> 00:34:43,560
I'd have sent you back long ago, believe me.

567
00:34:44,560 --> 00:34:46,040
Xiao Min may be gone,

568
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:47,920
but her grave

569
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:50,000
is still back home, isn't it?

570
00:34:50,320 --> 00:34:51,880
Fallen leaves must return to their roots.

571
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:54,600
This place is your root.

572
00:34:56,320 --> 00:34:57,520
Where else would you go?

573
00:34:58,080 --> 00:34:59,320
And even if worst comes to worst,

574
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:03,400
I'll take care of you till the end.

575
00:35:04,520 --> 00:35:06,320
And if I can't, there's still Xuan Yan.

576
00:35:07,160 --> 00:35:09,200
Xuan Yan is like your own son too.

577
00:35:12,800 --> 00:35:14,960
I appreciate the thought,

578
00:35:16,840 --> 00:35:19,680
but I've got nothing to do around here.

579
00:35:21,240 --> 00:35:23,680
The moment cultural products came up, I got scared.

580
00:35:24,320 --> 00:35:26,240
This is exactly the ending I feared.

581
00:35:27,120 --> 00:35:29,000
What you fear most always happens.

582
00:35:30,240 --> 00:35:31,600
Now that it's come to this,

583
00:35:32,840 --> 00:35:34,800
I need to make my own plans.

584
00:35:34,920 --> 00:35:36,080
Anyone else can leave,

585
00:35:37,840 --> 00:35:39,400
but you can't.

586
00:35:39,720 --> 00:35:41,480
I'm looking after you for life.

587
00:35:43,600 --> 00:35:45,040
Do you remember, back then,

588
00:35:45,560 --> 00:35:47,840
the day we both left Hongxing Factory,

589
00:35:48,440 --> 00:35:50,560
carrying our bedrolls out the door?

590
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:52,680
Remember what you said to me?

591
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:53,680
Yongnian!

592
00:35:55,600 --> 00:35:56,280
Yongnian!

593
00:35:56,640 --> 00:35:57,480
Wait for me!

594
00:35:59,200 --> 00:36:00,000
What are you doing?

595
00:36:00,840 --> 00:36:01,520
I'm quitting my job.

596
00:36:01,520 --> 00:36:02,640
What's it got to do with you?

597
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:05,080
This is a state-run factory, you know?

598
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:06,920
It's an iron rice bowl. It'll support you for life.

599
00:36:06,920 --> 00:36:07,440
Go back.

600
00:36:07,440 --> 00:36:08,520
Do you remember

601
00:36:08,600 --> 00:36:10,200
what we swore when we were kids?

602
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:12,200
In this life, we live together

603
00:36:12,200 --> 00:36:13,520
and we die together.

604
00:36:13,600 --> 00:36:15,520
You want to go start your own factory?

605
00:36:16,120 --> 00:36:17,480
I'm coming with you.

606
00:36:20,680 --> 00:36:21,800
Business isn't easy.

607
00:36:22,600 --> 00:36:23,640
What if we lose everything?

608
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:25,400
You'd starve alongside me?

609
00:36:25,520 --> 00:36:26,520
Even if we lose, I'm not afraid.

610
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:28,600
If we strip all the Qingtan bark,

611
00:36:28,600 --> 00:36:30,400
I'll bundle up the sticks and sell them as firewood.

612
00:36:30,600 --> 00:36:32,120
We can grow our own Shatian rice.

613
00:36:32,480 --> 00:36:33,400
If the paper won't sell,

614
00:36:33,800 --> 00:36:35,400
at least we'll still have food.

615
00:36:36,200 --> 00:36:37,200
We won't go hungry.

616
00:36:43,720 --> 00:36:44,200
Let's go.

617
00:36:47,440 --> 00:36:50,080
Those were just silly words from our youth.

618
00:36:50,080 --> 00:36:51,280
They don't count.

619
00:36:52,080 --> 00:36:53,960
No, how can you call them silly?

620
00:36:55,040 --> 00:36:58,320
That's the backbone and spirit of the Xuan Family.

621
00:36:59,200 --> 00:37:00,520
I'm not an educated man,

622
00:37:01,320 --> 00:37:02,280
but I know one thing:

623
00:37:04,000 --> 00:37:05,200
it's that spirit

624
00:37:06,320 --> 00:37:08,120
that's kept the Xuan Family going till today.

625
00:37:08,800 --> 00:37:11,120
Even if the Xuan Family is struggling now,

626
00:37:11,120 --> 00:37:12,960
we can't lose that spirit.

627
00:37:13,400 --> 00:37:14,360
It's not outdated.

628
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:18,440
What are we, you and me?

629
00:37:19,720 --> 00:37:21,120
You came to the Xuan Family at twelve,

630
00:37:21,120 --> 00:37:22,520
took my father as your master.

631
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:25,520
We ate, slept, played, and worked together.

632
00:37:26,680 --> 00:37:28,280
We may not be blood brothers,

633
00:37:30,240 --> 00:37:32,080
but we are brothers all the same.

634
00:37:38,080 --> 00:37:39,320
Don't do this.

635
00:37:39,520 --> 00:37:40,640
These two old brothers

636
00:37:40,960 --> 00:37:42,840
have worked hard their whole lives.

637
00:37:45,960 --> 00:37:47,160
Now we're old,

638
00:37:49,640 --> 00:37:51,640
it's time to enjoy our retirement.

639
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:54,720
Eat whatever you want,

640
00:37:55,520 --> 00:37:58,600
have fun however you please.

641
00:37:59,680 --> 00:38:01,520
That's the life of us old folks.

642
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:11,920
The first time I came here as a kid,

643
00:38:13,440 --> 00:38:14,480
Uncle Lin was already here.

644
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:17,360
Decades have passed.

645
00:38:18,280 --> 00:38:19,480
Uncle Lin is just like

646
00:38:19,640 --> 00:38:21,480
the blue sandalwood trees on this hill,

647
00:38:22,040 --> 00:38:23,360
quiet and unassuming,

648
00:38:23,800 --> 00:38:24,880
but always there.

649
00:38:26,320 --> 00:38:27,520
It's time he had a rest.

650
00:38:28,520 --> 00:38:30,720
When he left for his son's place in Shanghai,

651
00:38:31,640 --> 00:38:33,680
he took a blue sandalwood sapling with him.

652
00:38:34,640 --> 00:38:35,480
He said

653
00:38:36,720 --> 00:38:37,880
once he got there,

654
00:38:38,560 --> 00:38:40,280
he'd have no one to talk to.

655
00:38:42,120 --> 00:38:43,360
Maybe the sandalwood tree

656
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:45,840
is his truest friend.

657
00:38:47,920 --> 00:38:48,920
Uncle Lin once told me,

658
00:38:49,560 --> 00:38:52,440
when his ancestors fell on hard times with nothing to eat,

659
00:38:53,200 --> 00:38:56,720
the Xuan Family's forefathers entrusted this drying field

660
00:38:57,320 --> 00:38:59,080
to his ancestors to manage.

661
00:38:59,560 --> 00:39:01,200
That's how his family survived,

662
00:39:01,720 --> 00:39:03,880
and had generations of descendants.

663
00:39:05,200 --> 00:39:06,720
So the Lin family's duty

664
00:39:07,040 --> 00:39:10,040
is to guard this drying field for the Xuan Family.

665
00:39:11,000 --> 00:39:14,040
This is the Xuan Family's root, across generations.

666
00:39:15,520 --> 00:39:16,480
From his teens

667
00:39:17,480 --> 00:39:18,520
until his old age,

668
00:39:19,320 --> 00:39:21,600
Uncle Lin never left this drying field.

669
00:39:22,840 --> 00:39:26,680
He lived his life like a sandalwood tree.

670
00:39:30,160 --> 00:39:31,600
When trusted with a task,

671
00:39:32,160 --> 00:39:33,520
you see it through faithfully.

672
00:39:35,880 --> 00:39:37,520
Maybe to Uncle Lin,

673
00:39:38,160 --> 00:39:40,480
this charge passed down from his ancestors

674
00:39:41,040 --> 00:39:42,960
was an even heavier responsibility.

675
00:39:44,040 --> 00:39:45,000
You know,

676
00:39:45,520 --> 00:39:46,840
in Uncle Lin's lifetime,

677
00:39:47,160 --> 00:39:48,760
the bark and straw he carried

678
00:39:49,080 --> 00:39:51,200
weighed more than this whole mountain.

679
00:39:52,160 --> 00:39:53,520
But every single time,

680
00:39:54,280 --> 00:39:55,800
he'd carry it step

681
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:57,640
by step.

682
00:39:58,600 --> 00:40:00,160
He carried loads like that his whole life.

683
00:40:01,840 --> 00:40:03,120
When Uncle Lin told my dad

684
00:40:03,120 --> 00:40:05,520
he was retiring back to Shanghai,

685
00:40:05,880 --> 00:40:07,120
you know what my dad said?

686
00:40:07,960 --> 00:40:09,160
My dad said,

687
00:40:10,040 --> 00:40:11,560
"The best bark craftsman

688
00:40:11,560 --> 00:40:12,840
in our Peach Blossom Town

689
00:40:13,040 --> 00:40:13,680
is gone."

690
00:40:15,360 --> 00:40:16,200
Do you know

691
00:40:16,600 --> 00:40:19,040
the difference between handmade and machine-made paper?

692
00:40:23,320 --> 00:40:25,200
Within the fibers of handmade paper

693
00:40:25,760 --> 00:40:28,360
flows the lifelong dedication

694
00:40:28,520 --> 00:40:31,680
of many people like Uncle Lin.

695
00:40:35,320 --> 00:40:36,320
Not bad.

696
00:40:39,280 --> 00:40:41,320
Your time here hasn't been wasted.

697
00:40:41,360 --> 00:40:43,800
Come, tell me what you've learned.

698
00:40:51,360 --> 00:40:52,680
The "way" in "ancient way"

699
00:40:54,160 --> 00:40:55,400
isn't just a method.

700
00:40:55,920 --> 00:40:57,000
It's not a gimmick.

701
00:40:57,200 --> 00:40:58,560
It's not clinging to the past.

702
00:40:58,920 --> 00:41:00,960
It's the sweat and heart of generations past.

703
00:41:00,960 --> 00:41:02,000
It's the sweat and heart of generations past.

704
00:41:02,600 --> 00:41:04,200
As long as that devotion lives on,

705
00:41:04,800 --> 00:41:07,520
as long as that spirit is passed down,

706
00:41:07,520 --> 00:41:10,440
then the paper made is the finest ancient-way paper.

707
00:41:11,120 --> 00:41:12,240
That's precisely why

708
00:41:12,520 --> 00:41:14,560
the Xuan Family's paper is so precious,

709
00:41:15,200 --> 00:41:17,160
and why the Xuan Family has lasted a thousand years.

710
00:41:24,680 --> 00:41:26,200
It's just such a pity

711
00:41:29,520 --> 00:41:32,080
the thousand-year Xuan Family no longer makes paper.

712
00:41:39,120 --> 00:41:42,120
I restructured the factory's business,

713
00:41:43,120 --> 00:41:44,800
switched to cultural creative products.

714
00:41:45,520 --> 00:41:46,960
The master craftsmen disagreed,

715
00:41:47,520 --> 00:41:48,520
so they all left.

716
00:41:56,520 --> 00:41:57,440
Do you think

717
00:41:58,640 --> 00:42:00,440
taking the Xuan paper creative product route

718
00:42:01,520 --> 00:42:02,520
was the wrong choice?

719
00:42:06,960 --> 00:42:07,760
I wasn't wrong.

720
00:42:08,960 --> 00:42:10,880
But I lost the roots of Xuan paper.

721
00:42:21,120 --> 00:42:22,880
Enough, don't overthink it.

722
00:42:23,320 --> 00:42:24,320
Since you're here,

723
00:42:24,680 --> 00:42:26,880
set aside the work on your plate,

724
00:42:27,120 --> 00:42:29,080
and let the thoughts in your head rest.

725
00:42:30,520 --> 00:42:31,560
I'll tell you honestly,

726
00:42:32,960 --> 00:42:34,320
the reason I chose to come here

727
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:37,920
was because I heard about your childhood,

728
00:42:38,080 --> 00:42:39,680
those three years you spent at the drying field.

729
00:42:40,160 --> 00:42:42,040
You, Xuan Yan, guided me.

730
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:44,360
You can guide yourself, too.

731
00:42:53,960 --> 00:42:54,480
Alright.

732
00:42:54,640 --> 00:42:55,720
Then let's join together

733
00:42:55,720 --> 00:42:57,960
and revive the Xuan Family.
